            <section>
               <title value="Hospital Course"/>
               <code>
                  <coding>
                     <system value="http://loinc.org"/>
                     <code value="8648-8"/>
                     <display value="Hospital Course"/>
                  </coding>
               </code>
               <text>
                  <status value="generated"/>
                  <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Dear colleague, I am writing to inform you regarding our mutual patient, a 90-year-old gentleman admitted under our care for investigation and management of a sleep disorder. Following admission, a thorough clinical assessment was conducted, including a detailed sleep history, cognitive screening, and review of his current medication regimen for potential contributing factors. Polysomnography was arranged to objectively characterise his sleep architecture. Blood investigations were performed to exclude secondary causes such as thyroid dysfunction, anaemia, and metabolic disturbance. No significant correctable organic aetiology was identified. Management included sleep hygiene education, structured behavioural advice, and cautious short-term pharmacological support given his age and associated risks. He was discharged in a stable and improved condition. I would kindly recommend continued monitoring of his sleep pattern in primary care and review of any ongoing contributing factors. Please do not hesitate to contact me should you require further information.</div>
               </text>
            </section>
